ide with original quotes and insightful strategies was written by a former corporate manager and VP turned author - R. Lance Sheridan.<br>
<br>
Bits and Pieces to Ponder is essentially a book composed of 'bits and pieces' of the author's personal experiences and observations, both in life and at work. These helped to serve as a guide in writing his book. <br>
<br>
R. Lance Sheridan prefaces his book with a description of an inspirational gift that he received from his parents. That gift was an album containing photographs of his ancestors that were carefully selected from boxes of old pictures. Those 'bits and pieces' of his family history were brought together to form a complete photo album much in the same way that Sheridan's individual phrases are brought together to form his book.<br>
<br>
Written with a refreshing simplicity, his pocket-sized book contains 365 short phrases, reflections, and words of wisdom for everyday life.  Wonderful advice resonates with such passages as, 'Cultivate the seed, not the fertilizer'; 'Set aside a pat on the back for a rainy day'; and 'Progress is secondary to incentive'. Whatever the page that is chosen, the thought can be pondered upon in terms of the reader's own experiences, or serve as a guide for the future. <br>
<br>
R. Lance Sheridan's love of words and their oddities, as well as his playful humor, make a thoughtful and enjoyable reading experience.  Visit the author’s website at <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>www.rlsheridan.com</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to read reviews; readers’ views; learn more about the book and how it might improve your life; and information on how to purchase a copy.<br>
